  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>RepairQ allows users to attach, or bundle, items within a ticket. When an item is bundled under another item on a ticket, the price of the bundled item does not contribute to the overall ticket total. Instead, the cost of the bundled item, referred to as the Child Item, becomes integrated into the existing parent item\u2019s price.</p><p>To ensure that a part is bundled under a labor/service, you can flag the Parent Item to require a bundled item before saving the ticket. You can also assign specific ticket statuses that restrict advancement until an item flagged as \u201cBundle Required\u201d is added to the ticket. This ensures that tickets cannot advance until all required labor and parts have been bundled.</p><p><strong>Bundle Required Item</strong>- If a Catalog Item is flagged with \u201cBundle Required,\u201d a Child Item must be bundled under it to save the ticket.  The Parent Item must have the following attributes for a bundle requirement:</p><ul><li><p>Create or update an existing Item Type with <strong>Labor </strong>and <strong>Bundle (as parent) </strong>attributes. </p></li><li><p>Enable the <strong>Bundle Required</strong> attribute for the Catalog Item. This enforces the bundling requirement.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Bundle Required Ticket Status</strong> - The ticket cannot advance to the assigned status unless an item flagged as \u201cBundle Required\u201d is added to the ticket.</p><ul><li><p>If you require a bundle for a Ticket Status, this is managed in <strong>Ticket General Settings</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Bundle requirements on tickets are managed at the Company or Location level.</p></li></ul><h3 id=\"BundleRequired:ItemsandTicketStatus-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932329027/Creating+a+New+Item+Type\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932329027\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Creating a New Item Type</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932329061/Create+a+Catalog+Item\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932329061\" data-linked-resource-version=\"12\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Creating a Catalog Item</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932787785/Catalog+Items+Bundle+Setup\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932787785\" data-linked-resource-version=\"21\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Catalog Items: Bundle Setup</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/2837905412\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bundling Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932591125/Catalog+Items+Device+Compatibility\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932591125\" data-linked-resource-version=\"16\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Catalog Items: Device Compatibility</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2057601121/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"BundleRequired:ItemsandTicketStatus-VerifytheItemTypeisCompatiblewithBundleRequired\">Verify the Item Type is Compatible with Bundle Required</h2><p>An Admin will need to log into your RepairQ environment to confirm this. From the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Settings </strong>\u2192 <strong>Company Settings</strong>. On the Company Settings Overview page, scroll down to the Catalog section and click on <strong>Item Types</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2057601121/Bundle%20Required%201.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2057601121/Bundle%20Required%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>At your discretion, edit an existing Item Type, and apply the <strong>Labor </strong>and <strong>Bundle (as parent) </strong>attributes.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: You may also decide to create a new Item Type for this purpose. If you create a new type, don\u2019t forget to an applicable<a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933410332/Setting+up+and+Assigning+Tax+Rates\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933410332\" data-linked-resource-version=\"20\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\"> Tax Rate</a>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2057601121/Bundle%20Required%203.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"BundleRequired:ItemsandTicketStatus-AddaBundleRequirementtoaCatalogItem\">Add a Bundle Requirement to a Catalog Item</h2><p>Search your catalog for an existing labor item for bundling. Make sure the assigned Item Type is the same type flagged as <strong>Labor </strong>and <strong>Bundle (as parent)</strong>, as mentioned above. Scroll down until you see the <strong>Bundle Required</strong> field, and select this field. When you are finished, <strong>Save </strong>your changes.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: To add a new labor item, follow the standard <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932329061/Create+a+Catalog+Item\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932329061\" data-linked-resource-version=\"12\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Catalog Item Creation Process</a>. After saving your changes for the new item, edit the catalog item, and the Bundle Required flag will appear. </p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"296\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2057601121/Bundle%20Required%204.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"300\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2057601121/Bundle%20Required%205.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"BundleRequired:ItemsandTicketStatus-BundleRequiredLaborItemsonTickets\">Bundle Required Labor Items on Tickets</h2><p>When you add a service/labor item to a ticket that requires a bundled item, you are notified when adding the item via the Smart Search feature as well as after the item is added to the ticket. The ticket can be saved without a bundled item, however, the option to move the ticket into Closed status is not allowed until a child item is bundled under the parent labor item.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"442\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2057601121/Bundle%20Required%206.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2057601121/Bundle%20Required%207.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"BundleRequired:ItemsandTicketStatus-BundleRequiredTicketStatus\">Bundle Required Ticket Status</h2><p>Once you\u2019ve established a bundle requirement, you can also assign specific ticket statuses that restrict advancement until an item flagged as \u201cBundle Required\u201d is added to the ticket. This ensures that tickets cannot advance until all required labor parts have been bundled.</p><p /><p>From the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Settings </strong>\u2192 <strong>Company Settings</strong>. On the Company Settings Overview page, scroll down to the Ticket section and click on <strong>General Settings</strong>.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: This feature is also available in Location Settings.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Bundle Required 1.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2057601121/Bundle%20Required%201.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Bundle Required 9.png\" width=\"682\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2057601121/Bundle%20Required%209.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>On the Ticket Settings page, scroll to the \u201cStatus Advancement Required Fields and Blockers\u201d<strong> </strong>section. Turn ON the setting next to <strong>Prevent from Advancing to the Following Ticket Statuses</strong> and add the applicable ticket statuses in the Ticket Status field. When finished, <strong>Save </strong>your changes.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Bundle Required 10.png\" width=\"475\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2057601121/Bundle%20Required%2010.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.21.X</p>",
